---
import { Image } from "@astrojs/image/components";
import ByteCapsule from "../assets/bytecapsuleit.jpeg";
import WIYP from "../assets/wellington.png";
import Fiverr from "../assets/fiverr-logo.png";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon";
---

<section
  class="my-10 w-full border-l border-gray-300 p-3 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center md:items-start"
>
  <h1 class="text-red-400 text-xl font-semibold mr-10">Experience</h1>
  <div class="flex flex-col space-y-10">
    <!-- Experience 3 -->
    <div class="">
      <div class="flex justify-between w-full">
        <div class="flex flex-col md:border-l md:border-gray-300">
          <div class="mx-5">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-1">
              <Image
                src={Fiverr}
                alt="Fiverr Logo"
                class="h-6 w-6 mr-2"
                fit="cover"
                format="avif"
              />
              <h1 class="text-lg font-semibold flex items-center">
                Fiverr
                <span>
                  <a href="https://fiverr.com/" target="_blank">
                    <Icon
                      name="gridicons:external"
                      class="ml-2 text-red-400"
                      width="18"
                    />
                  </a>
                </span>
              </h1>
            </div>
            <h3>Level 2 Seller</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-600">Sept, 2022 - Present</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ml-5 mt-4">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
          I am a Level 2 seller on Fiverr, excels in AWS DevOps and MERN stack
          development. I expertly design, deploy, and manage AWS infrastructure,
          focusing on serverless applications using Docker, EC2, ECS, Lambda,
          API Gateway, and DynamoDB. My proficiency in the MERN stack spans
          MongoDB, Express.js, React, and Node.js, evident in deploying
          e-commerce, web applications, and APIs on AWS while addressing
          performance and security concerns. My knack for problem-solving and
          efficiency ensures top-notch solutions in both AWS and MERN stack
          domains.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Experience 2 -->
    <div class="">
      <div class="flex justify-between w-full">
        <div class="flex flex-col">
          <div class="mx-5">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-1">
              <Image
                src={WIYP}
                alt="Wellington Logo"
                class="h-6 w-6 mr-2"
                fit="cover"
                format="avif"
              />
              <h1 class="text-lg font-semibold flex items-center">
                Wellington In Your Pocket
                <span>
                  <a
                    href="https://wellingtoninyourpocket.co.nz/home2/"
                    target="_blank"
                  >
                    <Icon
                      name="gridicons:external"
                      class="ml-2 text-red-400"
                      width="18"
                    />
                  </a>
                </span>
              </h1>
            </div>
            <h3>Cloud Engineer</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-600">Jan, 2023 - Sept, 2023</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ml-5 mt-4">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
          As a Cloud Engineer at "Wellington In Your Pocket", My role involves
          designing, implementing, and maintaining the backend architecture
          using various AWS services. I am responsible for ensuring scalability,
          reliability, and security of the cloud infrastructure to support the
          application's requirements. I work closely with cross-functional teams
          to understand project requirements and translate them into scalable
          and robust cloud solutions that drive the application's success.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Experience 1 -->
    <div class="">
      <div class="flex justify-between w-full">
        <div class="flex flex-col">
          <div class="mx-5">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-1">
              <Image
                src={ByteCapsule}
                alt="Bytecapsule Logo"
                class="h-6 w-6 mr-2"
                aspectRatio={1 / 1}
                fit="cover"
                format="avif"
              />
              <h1 class="text-lg font-semibold flex items-center">
                Byte Capsule Ltd.
                <span>
                  <a href="https://www.bytecapsuleit.com/" target="_blank">
                    <Icon
                      name="gridicons:external"
                      class="ml-2 text-red-400"
                      width="18"
                    />
                  </a>
                </span>
              </h1>
            </div>
            <h3>Operations Lead</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-600">May, 2020 - Nov, 2022</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ml-5 mt-4">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
          <!-- As a Operations Lead at Byte Capsule Ltd, I had to wear multiple hats
          in the startup environment. I have provided Appliaction security
          services to the clients, Teaches Cyber Security to thousands of
          students, Improved companys operations attended various events as a
          public speaker. I coccaborated with other team members to provide
          customers their expected services. -->

           During my tenure as an Operations Lead at Byte Capsule Ltd, I undertook
          multifaceted responsibilities within the dynamic startup landscape. My
          roles encompassed delivering comprehensive Application Security services
          to our clients, educating and mentoring thousands of students in Cyber
          Security, optimizing company operations, and participating as a keynote
          speaker at diverse industry events. Collaborating seamlessly with cross-functional
          teams, I ensured the seamless delivery of anticipated services to our valued
          customers.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
